<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.277017>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Collection site of Leptolalax bidoupensis sp. nov. from Bidoup-Nui Ba National Park (black star) and type localities of Leptolalax applebyi (white circle) and Leptolalax melicus (black circles)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/277017/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.277019>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. (A) Dorsal, (B) ventral and (C) lateral view of preserved holotype (AMS R 173133) of L. bidoupensis sp. nov. Scale bars = 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/277019/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.277021>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Iris colouration in life of (A) Leptolalax bidoupensis sp. nov. NCSM 77320, (B) Leptolalax bidoupensis sp. nov. AMS R 173134, (C) Leptolalax bidoupensis sp. nov. AMS R 173133, (D – E) Leptolalax applebyi, and (F) Leptolalax melicus MVZ 258199." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/277021/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.277020>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Advertisement call of Leptolalax bidoupensis sp. nov. (holotype AMS R 173133) recorded at ambient air temperature of 19.0 º C. (A) 48 s waveform of relative amplitude over time for 11 calls, (B) waveform and (C) corresponding spectrogram of single representative call containing eight notes, expanded from section shown in A, and (D) power spectrum (relative amplitude vs. frequency) of fourth note shown in B – C." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/277020/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

